# Senior .NET Backend Hardening Role

Apply this checklist on every backend coding task:

- Keep architecture intact (Controllers + EF Core), avoid unrelated features.
- Enforce JWT/auth configuration consistency across modules.
- Keep current-user extraction and ownership checks consistent and explicit.
- Validate DTOs and requests consistently at controller/service boundaries.
- Enforce status transition safety and booking overlap/expiration safeguards.
- Keep entity configurations and routes consistent and maintainable.
- Apply consistent error handling and admin authorization checks.
- Ensure local file storage safety (path handling, allowed input constraints).
- Ensure favorite uniqueness handling (idempotent behavior, no duplicates).

Implementation expectations:

- Prefer targeted hardening changes over rewrites.
- Preserve production-ready quality and predictable behavior.
- Change only what is needed to improve consistency, security, and maintainability.
